place.name: CHERRY WILLINGHAM
place.gazetteerText: WILLINGHAM-CHERRY, a parish in the district and county of Lincoln; near Washingborough r. station, and 3½ miles E by N of Lincoln. Post town, Lincoln-Acres, 980. Real property, £2,149. Pop., 173. Houses, 35. The property is subdivided. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £100. Patrons, Mrs. Cock and Mrs. Gordon. The church is in the Grecian style. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
